{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "23", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "10", "M": "51", "S": "45"}}, "news": [{"title": "Goa: Karapur protest against housing project enters day 78", "para": "Villagers in Karapur are continuing their 78-day protest against a mega housing project, alleging environmental norm violations.  Under the Karapur Gramastha Ekvoticho Aawaz banner, residents, including resolute women, are staging a sit-in.  A tree-planting drive was initiated on Sunday in cleared areas, with hopes of wildlife returning to the restored ecosystem, as evidenced by a peacock sighting.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/day-78-of-karapur-housing-project-protest-villagers-stand-firm/131926275?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-5615618/131926275.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Ahmedabad civic body cannot revoke its own regularisation orders: Gujarat HC", "para": "The Gujarat High Court has ruled that once an authority grants or denies regularization of unauthorized construction by accepting an impact fee, it cannot later revoke that decision. The court quashed an Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation order that canceled a prior regularization, stating the authority lacked jurisdiction for such a review. This decision protects property owners from arbitrary cancellations after regularization.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/gujarat-high-court-rules-ahmedabad-civic-body-cannot-cancel-regularization-orders/131926214?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-295602/131926214.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Staff crunch leaves Ahmedabad civic body struggling to collect nominal property rents", "para": "Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation is facing a significant revenue loss as thousands of prime commercial properties are leased for as little as Rs 100-500 monthly.  A severe staff shortage has hampered rent collection, with many properties in disrepair.  To address this, the AMC is launching a digital overhaul and prioritizing redevelopment of underutilized prime real estate to boost commercial potential.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/ahmedabad-civic-body-struggles-to-collect-low-property-rents-amid-staff-shortage/131925679?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-460785/131925679.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}